            <quote source="#bib5098-3">Hormizd succeeded his father Khosrow as ruler of the Sasanian Empire in early 579. The sources describe him as a tyrant who was highly unpopular in Persia and who broke off the peace negotiations with the Romans. He was overthrown in early 590 when one of his generals revolted against him.</quote>
